recalls.Summary: General Motors, LLC (GM) is recalling certain 2023–2026 Chevrolet Corvette vehicles equipped with a left-side radiator/fan combination. Excess fuel may spill into the vehicle fuel-filler pocket during refueling and leak onto an ignition source.
recalls.Consequence: A fuel leak in the presence of an ignition source, such as hot engine or exhaust components, can increase the risk of a fire.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will install a shield to divert spilled fuel, free of charge. Owner notification letters were mailed November 14, 2025. Owners may contact Chevrolet customer service at 1-800-222-1020. GM's number for this recall is N252514930.

complaints.summary: The contact owns a 2023 Chevrolet Corvette. The contact received notification of NHTSA Campaign Number: 25V536000 (Fuel System, Gasoline); however, the part to do the recall repair was not yet available. The contact stated that the manufacturer had exceeded a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair. The dealer was made aware of the issue and confirmed that parts were not yet available. The manufacturer was made aware of the issue and confirmed that parts were not yet available. The contact had not experienced a failure.

On 10/13 after refuling my 2023 Chevy Corvette. I was cruising on a freeway when the car started showing signs of staying in 5th gear. The rev limiter was going from 500 to 2500 rpm rhythmically at a cruising speed of 65mph. At this time, I noticed the loss of response from the gas pedal. The car was then placed in manual shifting mode so that i can attempt to regain population control and maintain the flow of traffic as this was a high crash area. Unfortunately, this attempt did not work and the dash cluster illuminated with the following alerts "rear axil system offline" "idle creep disabled," "service transmission" at this time. The gear indicator on the dash that shows the mode and gear, for example: D3 (drive 3rd gear), completely disappeared and the gas pedal completely went unresponsive. At this point i used the momentum of the car in motion to exit off of the freeway into a parking center. The vehicle proceeded to not respond in regards to going into park, reverse, or drive. The only thing that worked was the electronic parking brake. This was a very scary situation that, without my federal law enforcement driving training I may not have coasted safely out of traffic.

My fiancé, [XXX]   died on [XXX], while driving his 2023 Chevrolet Corvette Z06 Convertible . He was passing another car on a straight road ,A witness confirmed he was not speeding excessively. Suddenly, he lost control of the vehicle, crashed, and the car burst into flames. I’ve since learned that GM issued a recall for this model due to fuel spillage and fire risk. Other owners have reported transmission and instrument panel failures. I believe a defect in the vehicle may have caused or contributed to [XXX] ’s death. I am requesting a formal investigation into this incident and the safety of the 2023 Corvette Z06. I am also pursuing legal action to hold GM accountable.   INFORMATION REDACTED PURSUANT TO THE FREEDOM OF INFORMATION ACT (FOIA), 5 U.S.C. 552(B)(6)

Shortly after purchasing the vehicle at the local Carson City,NV CHEVROLET dealer on 5/18/2025 my passenger started to hear a muffled “thumping noise” from the right front foot well? I am a disabled veteran USAF pilot with hearing loss and did not immediately hear it. The car had 29,129 miles on it when purchased and was a “certified vehicle” with some remaining original warranty as well as an extended warranty given its great condition(I was told!) After a few hundred miles of driving the sound became much louder and VERY noticeable when even on rough roads I discovered when removing the “frunk” trim to investigate a weak battery up front that an aluminum upper suspension right front shock mount was only being retained by a single bolt of the FOUR designed to secure it! Two had sheared the aluminum mount off and one bolt had broken off and was missing! The car has been in possession of the dealer since I had it towed in 6/27/2025 I have had NO RESPONSE from the dealer as to the cause.other than to indicate that it had been a rental car company acquisition No other external body/suspension/tire/fender damage was visible  The dealer has confirmed the failure and has to my knowledge not repaired it although they did indicate that GM engineers were advised?

On 8/3/2025 I was at a stop light. It turned green. I went to go and my car would not go past first gear. Had to pull over. Waited turned the car off. Turned it back on and started driving, then I got an alert 545. Then my entire screen went blank only showing the alert. I called my dealership to explain. They said there were recalls on the 2023 and 2024 transmissions. That’s why I got the alert 545. But they said there was nothing they could do. I could bring it in for a test drive with a technician and if it pops up alert 545 then they would submit a ticket to GM. But the earliest to fix my corvette would be October. But also saying I would have to pay full price for everything. I bought my 2023 Corvette 1LT C8 stingray in 2022 and have only put 19,000 miles on it. I do not miss maintenance or anything. I’m not sure how to get GM to pay for my transmission and labor. It also would not let me acknowledge and click the button on the steering wheel. My display went off and I could not get it back on even turning the knob. This is incredibly dangerous for my safety. Transmission failure. Can’t see the speed I’m going.
The passenger seat belt locks and pins the passenger down.  It will not release unless it’s released from the release button.  If there’s an accident, my passenger would be seriously injured.
When drive slowly, sometimes it grinds really lound when the wheels are wet or dry. Took it to 2 different dealers, they said it's normal. I have video for both incidents.

While I was on vacation in Gatlinburg TN my vehicle parked in my home garage turned on by itself producing carbon monoxide in my property I reached out numerous times to GM and they failed to do anything about it. I have footage please assist thanks.

On [XXX] I was driving my corvette in Atlantic City, New Jersey, which at that time I noticed smoke coming from the rear of the vehicle. I looked at my dash to see if any warning lights or check engine lights were on and nothing Indicate there was a problem. So I did  continue to drive to get to a safe place where I can pull over and look at the engine. When I came up to the red light, the car next to me told me that my vehicle was on the fire. I was able to pull over on the side of road next to the hospital in Atlantic City. And then I got out of my car to nattempt to put out the fire myself as I noticed Melting Plastic that was on fire, was dripping all my tires to avoid the tires Catching on fire. I Remove the plastic that was on fire, causing burns to my hand. Then I called the fire to department to help me put out the fire. Once the fire was put out. I had it towed to the dealership they Told me to call my insurance company. Doing insurance process one of their technicians looked at the vehicle and determined that the rear Transmission case cracked from a Defective part in the transmission breaking, Which Cause the transmission fluid to pour out onto the exhaust system, Then the hot Transmission fluid ignite and set the rear of the car on fire. The insurance company liberty Mutual Refuse to fix the car due to mechanical malfunction. I then Contact General Motors and file a claim Which has been open for several months with zero repairs done to the vehicle. GM motors also sent a technician to look at the vehicle and came to the same conclusion but still has not  attempted to fix the vehicle. This vehicle with a Defect like this is very unsafe. I could’ve been driving on the parkway and the vehicle locked up because the transmission broke and caused an shi accident or the fire could’ve been a lot worse could’ve been burnt to death.  INFORMATION REDACTED PURSUANT TO THE FREEDOM OF INFORMATION ACT (FOIA), 5 U.S.C. 552(B)(6)

Normal driving conditions while in Z-mode in moderate traffic, an audible bang was heard, however there was no immediate issue. A few minutes later the Check Engine Light, ABS, Traction Control and other lights appear on dash.   Once lights appear, brakes fail and no longer slow the car down, the gas pedal only revved the car and could no longer accelerate. The car was still on and “driving”, I just didn’t have acceleration or brakes. I put my turn signal on and eventually was able to safely pull off the road and stop the vehicle utilizing Neutral and the Emergency Parking Brake. I was in genuine fear of crashing due to not having brakes or acceleration and felt that if the parking brake and/or neutral failed, then I’d have to crash to stop the vehicle.   Not having brakes or acceleration put myself, my passenger, and every vehicle around me when it occurred at risk of injury. This has occurred twice in less than 1 year of ownership with this vehicle and I’ve taken it to two dealerships, Mike Reichenbach Chevrolet and Rick Hendrick Chevrolet. When it first occurred in December 2023, I was also in Z-Mode in light traffic, after it occurred, I drove slowly to the dealership with the hazard lights on. The second time I brought it to a dealership was after the first dealership couldn’t find the cause nor replicate the issue. The codes were cleared by the first dealership, but the car was still operating roughly and not as designed. The third time, in July 2024, it was brought to Rick Hendrick Chevrolet where the service invoice says “GOOD POSSIBILITY THE AFTERMARKET GPS UNIT PLUGGED INTO THE DLC PORT IS SHORTING OUT THE VEHICLE COMMUNICATION CIRCUITS AND CAUSING INTERMITTENT ELECTRICAL ISSUES. MAY BE ALSO CAUSING BATTERY DRAIN ISSUE.” The device referred to is called Bouncie, I got it AFTER this first occurred and the service team there is blaming both of these occurrences on the device. No repair was performed as the issue couldn’t be replicated.

Put vehicle in reverse.  Vehicle would not move. Vehicle placed back in park. Put vehicle in reverse again; and after advanced acceleration heard a loud clunk sound and jarring movement. Car continued in reverse normally. Vehicle was put into drive and driven approximately 500 feet at which time vehicle shut down. Service transmission and “rear axle not engaged” messages showing, as well as an overheating message. Dealership unresponsive.

This is a 2023 Corvette 70th Anniversary Edition. Button to open door from drivers side doesn’t activate, needing to pull manual handle. Electric button to open hard top convertible doesn’t activate. Vehicle taken to dealer and inspected. According to inspection results, there is major components which controls these functions was ordered and received. Vehicle is at the dealer for repair.
The hood unexpectedly opens and can fly up and cause loss of forward vision.  The hood can fly off and cause death.  With no visibility the a collision can cause death.

The reverse camera works intermittently, but fails more often than it works properly. Able to reset by shutting car off and leaving door open for 90 seconds, then restarting. Works for that ignition/drive cycle but then becomes unreliable again after next startup.  Car is a week old. Have not brought to dealer yet for warranty claim, however as this is a required safety system I am reporting it.

The vehicle has had rear and front camera failure within 72 hours of me buying it (91 miles); and I let my sales guy know, we decided to bring it by the dealership one day when it is malfunctioning. I got it to act up that Saturday 3/18/23 with 123 miles, and it showed 2 DTC's (B1A62 and U0131), but with a limited staff, they had no one to look at it. Still not upset, I said whatever and figured I would just drive it and bring it back during the weekdays   It happened again this morning on the way to work, and I took it right in; they were able to scan it again and show the fault codes. This is where it gets really upsetting; the tool/adapter they need to test the AV cable is showing June 16th ship date. I sell cars for a living also, and this is something I would never expect a customer to just deal with and wait. I literally can't drive the car in and out of my driveway without the camera system. My wife almost ran into the door because the camera does not work. My fear is a child could be hit or run over, and I can't believe General Motors is ok with a new vehicle being sold, failing immediately after delivery, and having no way to fix the problem. I have contacted someone at GM corporate, and they also instructed me to wait for diagnostic. This is a concern on other Corvettes, and not the first instance of this happening.

The backup camera display will occasionally not display what is behind the vehicle (the screen is blank with a strange icon in the middle of it).  This is not a consistent problem. It sometimes works, and sometimes it doesn't.  I almost backed over a child who wasn't visible. In my research this problem also happens to other GM vehicles.

The contact owns a 2023 Chevrolet Corvette. The contact stated that while the vehicle was in reverse(R), the transmission failed to engage as the gear indicator light began to flash and the service transmission message was displayed on the instrument panel. After multiple attempts, the contact was able to engage the transmission and drove the vehicle to dealer where they were unable to diagnose or service the failure. The manufacturer was notified of the failure and a complaint was filed. The vehicle was not repaired. The failure mileage was 812.

Vet delivered 5/31/22. I noticed that the daylight driving lights came on when it was dark and headlights came on during the day, completely backwards when vehicle headlights switched to "auto" . Took vehicle to dealership and they replaced the dash light sensor but this did't fix the problem. Dealership notified Chevrolet regarding the problem. Went to the web page titled CorvetteForum.com and noticed other '23 Corvette owners with the same problem. It's been almost 6 months with "NO" word from Chevrolet as to when this issue will be resolved.

issues.title: Z07 Package Carbon Fiber Wheels Cracking
issues.description: Carbon fiber wheels included in the Z07 performance package are experiencing cracking under normal driving conditions, particularly around spoke areas and rim edges. This affects the structural integrity of the wheels and poses safety risks.
symptoms: visible cracks in carbon fiber wheel spokes
issues.fix_description: Complete wheel replacement with new carbon fiber wheels or switch to aluminum wheels. GM has issued replacements under warranty for affected units.
issues.prevention: Avoid aggressive curb contact, regular visual inspections, proper tire pressure maintenance

issues.title: LT6 Engine Oil Consumption Issues
issues.description: The naturally aspirated 5.5L LT6 engine is experiencing excessive oil consumption, with some owners reporting consumption rates of 1 quart per 1000 miles or less, well above normal specifications.
issues.fix_description: Engine inspection for piston ring issues, potential engine rebuild or replacement under warranty coverage
issues.prevention: Regular oil level monitoring, using only recommended oil specifications, avoiding extended high-RPM operation during break-in

issues.title: Transmission Temperature Overheating
issues.description: The 8-speed dual-clutch transmission experiences overheating during track use or aggressive driving, causing the vehicle to enter protective mode and limiting performance.
issues.fix_description: Software updates to transmission cooling strategy, additional cooling modifications, or transmission fluid changes
issues.prevention: Allow proper warm-up periods, avoid extended track sessions without cooling breaks, monitor transmission temperature

issues.title: Front Splitter and Aerodynamics Package Damage
issues.description: The aggressive aerodynamics package, particularly the front splitter and side skirts, are prone to damage from normal road surfaces, parking lot approaches, and minor road debris.
symptoms: visible cracks in carbon fiber splitter
issues.fix_description: Replacement of damaged aerodynamic components, potential installation of protective elements
issues.prevention: Careful navigation of steep driveways, avoiding road debris, using front axle lift system when available

issues.title: Electronic Stability Control Malfunction
issues.description: Some vehicles experience ESC system malfunctions, causing unexpected intervention or failure to engage when needed, potentially affecting vehicle stability and safety.
issues.fix_description: Software updates to ESC module, sensor calibration, or replacement of stability control sensors
issues.prevention: Regular software updates, avoiding aggressive driving until system is verified functional

issues.title: Brake Rotor Warping and Premature Wear
issues.description: The high-performance Brembo carbon ceramic brakes are experiencing premature rotor warping and uneven wear patterns, particularly under track conditions or aggressive street driving.
issues.fix_description: Replacement of carbon ceramic rotors and brake pads, potential brake system inspection and upgrade
issues.prevention: Proper brake break-in procedure, avoid aggressive braking when brakes are cold, regular brake inspections

issues.title: Infotainment System Freezing and Reboot Issues
issues.description: The infotainment system experiences random freezing, slow response times, and unexpected reboots, affecting navigation, audio, and vehicle settings access.
issues.fix_description: Software updates, system reset procedures, or infotainment module replacement if hardware failure is confirmed
issues.prevention: Regular software updates, avoiding extreme temperature exposure, proper system shutdown procedures

issues.title: Paint Quality and Clear Coat Issues
issues.description: Some vehicles exhibit paint defects including orange peel texture, clear coat separation, and premature fading or discoloration, particularly on carbon fiber body panels.
symptoms: visible paint defects under certain lighting
issues.fix_description: Panel repainting or refinishing, clear coat reapplication, potential full vehicle repaint in severe cases
issues.prevention: Regular washing and waxing, garage storage, UV protection, avoiding harsh chemicals

issues.title: Door Handle Operation Failures
issues.description: Electronic door handles are experiencing operation failures, preventing proper entry or exit from the vehicle, particularly in cold weather conditions.
symptoms: door won't unlock despite proper key fob signal
issues.fix_description: Door handle actuator replacement, software updates, or complete door handle assembly replacement
issues.prevention: Keep door handle area clean and dry, regular lubrication of mechanical components, avoid forceful operation

issues.title: Fuel Pump Pressure Irregularities
issues.description: Some vehicles experience fuel pump pressure inconsistencies, leading to performance issues, engine hesitation, or potential fuel starvation under high-performance driving conditions.
symptoms: loss of power at high RPM
issues.fix_description: Fuel pump replacement, fuel system inspection and cleaning, pressure regulator replacement
issues.prevention: Use high-quality fuel, avoid running on low fuel levels, regular fuel system maintenance

editorial.tagline: Mid-engine American fury meets naturally aspirated perfection
editorial.hero_blurb: The C8 Z06 delivers 670 horsepower from its screaming flat-plane crank V8, transforming America's sports car into a European supercar slayer. This is the Corvette that finally puts the engine where it belongs – behind the driver.
editorial.essence: The Z06 represents Corvette's most dramatic evolution, combining mid-engine architecture with the highest-revving production V8 GM has ever built. It's a track-focused weapon that maintains surprising daily usability while delivering supercar performance at a fraction of the price.
editorial.heritage: Born from the legendary Z06 lineage dating back to 1963, this generation breaks from tradition with its mid-engine layout while honoring the Z06's track-focused DNA. It's the culmination of decades of Corvette racing experience distilled into street-legal form.
editorial.design_philosophy: Designers prioritized aerodynamic efficiency and cooling over pure aesthetics, creating a purposeful machine that looks fast standing still. Every line serves the pursuit of downforce and heat management for sustained track performance.
editorial.motorsport_history: Developed alongside Corvette Racing's C8.R program, sharing fundamental architecture and lessons learned from IMSA competition. The Z06 brings genuine race car DNA to the street in unprecedented fashion for a production Corvette.
editorial.engine_character: The LT6 is a masterpiece of naturally aspirated fury, building power linearly to its 8,600 RPM redline with an intensity that makes turbocharged rivals feel lazy. It demands to be revved and rewards with intoxicating power delivery.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 8-speed dual-clutch transmission fires off shifts with precision and violence, offering paddle control that rivals the best European boxes. In track mode, it becomes an extension of your right foot.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: The mid-engine platform transforms Corvette handling from good to exceptional, with perfectly balanced weight distribution and adjustable suspension that adapts from comfortable cruiser to track weapon instantly.
editorial.steering_feel: Precise and well-weighted with excellent on-center feel, though it lacks the ultimate communication of the best hydraulic systems. The rack delivers confidence-inspiring accuracy at speed.
editorial.brake_confidence: Massive Brembo carbon ceramic brakes provide endless stopping power with pedal feel that builds trust immediately. They're virtually fade-free under track conditions while remaining manageable on the street.
editorial.sound_signature: The flat-plane crank V8 screams like a European exotic, abandoning traditional American V8 rumble for a high-pitched wail that climbs to Ferrari-like intensity at redline.
editorial.ideal_owner: Track day enthusiasts and serious drivers who want supercar performance without supercar prices or maintenance costs. Perfect for those who prioritize driving engagement over luxury amenities.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Buyers seeking maximum comfort, cargo space, or traditional V8 sound. Also not ideal for those who prefer manual transmissions or front-engine layouts.
editorial.buyers_summary: The Z06 delivers genuine supercar performance at a remarkable value, but availability remains challenging. Consider extended warranties and factor in potential dealer markups when budgeting.

expertReviews.title: HONEST REVIEW: 2026 CORVETTE Z06 3LZ... by Will Motivation
pros: Spectacular exterior styling with no bad angles
High-revving LT6 V8 engine that revs to 8600 RPM
Excellent sound quality
Good trunk storage space front and rear
Soft close feature on storage compartments
Highly adjustable seating with memory settings
Improved interior controls for 2026 with removal of button wall
Built-in Google Maps integration
Comfortable for 6'2" driver
cons: Limited storage space behind seats
Hand-stitched leather shows imperfections with zigzag stitching
Front proportions could be slightly better
expertReviews.verdict: The 2026 Corvette Z06 3LZ delivers spectacular exterior styling that rivals Ferrari and Lamborghini models, earning an 8.9/10 rating. The reviewer, who owns multiple supercars including Ferrari F8 and Porsche GT3, considers this legitimately competitive with exotic cars. The high-revving LT6 engine and excellent build quality make it a genuine supercar. Interior improvements for 2026 include removal of the button wall and better control layout.

expertReviews.title: 2 YEARS of C8 Corvette Z06 OWNERSHIP! Is it WORTH it ...
pros: 670hp naturally aspirated flat-plane crank V8
Top 5 car reviewer has driven
Supercar-like interior quality
Excellent reliability with only minor issues
Easy maintenance
Great value at under $120k
Paint and interior held up excellently over 12k miles
Comfortable competition seats
No engine problems or check engine lights
Strong resale value
cons: Limited availability of proper dealership maintenance
Can only drive 4-5 months per year in northern climates
Minor seat creasing issue
Passenger door panel rattle
Difficulty finding dealers experienced with alignment
expertReviews.verdict: After 2 years and 12,000 miles, the C8 Z06 proves to be one of the best cars the reviewer has driven, ranking in his top 5. Despite $70k in modifications, the car has been extremely reliable with only minor cosmetic issues that were promptly fixed under warranty. The 670hp naturally aspirated engine has been bulletproof, and maintenance is surprisingly easy for a mid-engine supercar. At current prices under $120k, it offers exceptional value and the reviewer strongly recommends it to anyone considering purchase.

pros: 670 horsepower flat-plane crank V8
Aggressive styling with functional aerodynamics
Convertible hard top mechanism
Carbon ceramic brakes

Michelin Pilot Sport Cup 2 tires
Front and rear storage space
Advanced technology features
cons: Very expensive starting at $128,000 base
$3,000 gas guzzler tax
Poor fuel economy (12 city/19 highway)
Premium fuel required
expertReviews.verdict: The 2025 Corvette Z06 is described as 'one of my favorite vehicles of all time' with gorgeous styling, advanced technology, and impressive performance features. The 5.5L flat-plane crank V8 produces 670 horsepower in a mid-engine platform with convertible capability. However, it comes at a premium price with additional options pushing costs significantly higher.

expertReviews.title: C8 Corvette Z06 Review || GAME OVER!
pros: 670 horsepower naturally aspirated LT6 engine with 8,600 RPM redline
Supercar performance at one-third the price of competitors
Exceptional cornering stability and handling dynamics
High-quality interior with both trunk and frunk storage
Addictive flat-plane crank sound
Advanced suspension geometry with subtle rear steering
cons: Tall 5th and 6th gear ratios hurt top-end acceleration
Electronic steering feels dead with poor feedback
Carbon ceramic brakes weak until up to temperature
expertReviews.verdict: The C8 Z06 delivers genuine supercar performance for a fraction of the cost, featuring a revolutionary 670hp naturally aspirated V8 with flat-plane crank that sounds incredible. While gear ratios and steering feel could be improved, this car fundamentally changes the game by offering Ferrari/McLaren performance at $145k fully loaded. It's a landmark achievement that makes exotic supercars hard to justify.

expertReviews.title: Corvette Z06 review: The most powerful NA V8 in the WORLD!
pros: Most powerful naturally aspirated V8 in the world (670 horsepower)
Flat-plane crank engine sounds incredible and is very responsive
Excellent suspension that handles bumps brilliantly on roads
Much better practicality than Porsche 911 with 357 liters of storage
Sharp steering and feels very planted in corners
cons: Dealers charging $50k over MSRP making it $150k total
Run-flat tires are expensive and labor-intensive to replace ($600 installation)
Long warm-up procedure before reaching full 8,500 RPM redline
Brakes feel over-assisted with poor progression
Doors open very wide making parking difficult
expertReviews.verdict: The Z06 is an exceptional track-focused Corvette with a screaming 5.5L flat-plane crank V8 that produces 670hp. While it has excellent performance, handling, and surprising road comfort, dealer markups of $50k over the $100k MSRP make it expensive. If you can get allocation at list price, it's a buy recommendation.

expertReviews.title: 2025 Corvette Z06 POV Review – This Supercar Will Blow ...
pros: America's answer to supercars at $100,000+ less than Ferrari/McLaren/Lamborghini
Naturally aspirated 670hp 5.5L V8 that revs to 8,500 RPM with amazing sound
Excellent performance - 0-60 in 2.6 seconds, quarter mile in 10.5 seconds
Driver-focused cockpit design with comfortable heated/cooled seats
Can be used as a daily driver with creature comforts like Bose audio
cons: Limited storage space for luggage
Only seats two people
Firm sport suspension feels road imperfections more in sport mode
expertReviews.verdict: The 2025 Corvette Z06 is America's true supercar answer to European exotics, delivering comparable track times and acceleration at a fraction of the cost. With its naturally aspirated 670hp V8, seamless 8-speed dual clutch transmission, and driver-focused design, it offers supercar performance that can be enjoyed daily. New for 2025 are 10-spoke wheels and Hysteria purple metallic color option.
